# CNAME Configuration Template
# ==========================================
# This file is used to configure a custom domain for your GitHub Pages site
# 
# Instructions:
# 1. Rename this file from "CNAME.example" to "CNAME" (no file extension)
# 2. Replace "example.com" below with your actual domain name
# 3. Configure DNS records with your domain provider
# 4. Commit and push the CNAME file to your repository
# 
# ==========================================

# Replace with your custom domain (one domain per line)
# Examples:
#   www.yourdomain.com
#   yourdomain.com
#   subdomain.yourdomain.com

example.com

# ==========================================
# DNS Configuration Steps:
# ==========================================
# 
# For Apex Domain (example.com):
# --------------------------------
# Add these A records to your DNS:
#   185.199.108.153
#   185.199.109.153
#   185.199.110.153
#   185.199.111.153
# 
# For WWW Subdomain (www.example.com):
# ------------------------------------
# Add a CNAME record:
#   CNAME: www.example.com → scotlaclair.github.io
# 
# For Other Subdomains (subdomain.example.com):
# ---------------------------------------------
# Add a CNAME record:
#   CNAME: subdomain.example.com → scotlaclair.github.io
# 
# ==========================================
# Verification:
# ==========================================
# 
# 1. After setting up DNS records, wait for propagation (can take 24-48 hours)
# 2. Check DNS propagation: https://dnschecker.org/
# 3. In GitHub repository settings, verify custom domain configuration:
#    Settings → Pages → Custom domain
# 4. Enable "Enforce HTTPS" once domain is verified
# 
# ==========================================
# Common Issues:
# ==========================================
# 
# - "Domain's DNS record could not be retrieved"
#   → Wait for DNS propagation or check DNS configuration
# 
# - "CNAME already taken"
#   → This domain is already used by another GitHub Pages site
# 
# - Certificate errors
#   → Wait for GitHub to provision SSL certificate (up to 24 hours)
# 
